{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b9b44a3-f098-4a0d-afc5-056926b24a0d","content":"Analyzing crash dumps is outside the scope of the available tools here (the `dump-collect` skill only covers **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them). Here's how you can analyze it yourself:\n\n**Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nThen inside the interactive session, try:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `threads` — list all threads\n\n**Using WinDbg** (Windows):\n1. Open the `.dmp` file in WinDbg\n2. Load SOS: `.loadby sos coreclr`\n3. Run `!pe` (print exception) and `!clrstack`\n\n**Using LLDB** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\n```\n\nWould you like help setting up any of these tools?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"889726b3-a8fb-4137-850d-cb236cc9ee13","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill isn't appropriate here. Let me provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":353},"id":"31442e15-f68c-4a59-abe7-6736dc43b5ae","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:05:48.583Z","parentId":"943833e9-3b9d-4870-957e-0b297e2bfcf6"}
